Stretching of Spacetime:

Original: [ ds^2 = -c^2 dt^2 + a(t)^2 \left( \frac{dr^2}{1 - k r^2} + r^2 (d\theta^2 + \sin^2\theta , d\phi^2) \right) ]

Causal Relativity:

Spatial metric without time: [ ds^2 = g_{ij} dx^i dx^j ]
Problem: For an expanding universe with (a(t) = t) and (k = 0), describe the spatial metric.

In this case: [ ds^2 = t^2 \left( dr^2 + r^2 (d\theta^2 + \sin^2\theta , d\phi^2) \right) ]
